{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, [613] removes finite elements in solid structures to modify the topology.",
    "Instead, [614] pursues design diversity.",
    "Here a NN surrogate model predicts near optimal structures from reference designs.",
    "The agent then learns to generate reference designs as input, such that the corresponding optimal structures are as diverse as possible.Also, high-dimensional PDEs have been solved with reinforcement learning [615,616].",
    "This is achieved by recasting the PDE into stochastic control problems, thereby solving these with reinforcement learning.Finally, adaptive mesh refinement algorithms have been learned by reinforcement learning [617]."
  ]
}